NOTES
Solar
energy
is
important
input
parameter
in
different
models
concerning
landscape,
vegetation,
evapotranspiration,
snowmelt
or
remote
sensing.
Solar
rays
incidence
angle
can
be
effectively
used
in
radiometric
corrections
in
hilly
terrain
where
very
precise
investigations
are
performed.
Incidence
angle
multiplied
by
solar
constant
(here
is
used
1370
kW
per
squared
meter)
gives
irradiance
which
can
be
computed
using
r.mapcalc.



